  "texts": [
    "Past work showed that the perceptions of public figures' warmth and competence can be extracted from an earlier LLM, Google's Word2Vec 26.",
    "Here we show that word embeddings extracted from GPT-3 23 can predict people's general sentiment toward public figures (likability) as well as their perceptions of their Big Five personality traits (openness, conscientiousness, extraversion, agreeableness, and emotional stability) that were shown to capture much variance in individual differences and reliably predict a wide range of individual and social outcomes 27.",
    "Our study focused on the 300 most popular public figures from 43 countries selected from among the 11,341 public figures listed in the Pantheon 1.0 dataset 28.",
    "Their popularity was approximated by their Wikipedia page views between 2008 and 2013.",
    "As artists were particularly popular, we limited their number to 100 to include public figures from seven other domains including business and law, exploration, humanities, institutions, science and technology, sports, and others."
  ],
